tox.ini.message:
Should be able to copy what is done for other test runs of:

commands = stestr run --slowest {posargs}

And actually, we should just move that into the base [testenv] commands since we override commands in any other jobs that do anything other than the default stestr run.

tools/rpm/centos/rpm.spec.message:
This is different from what the CentOS package does and in the case of rpmhome it possibly removes more files.  The lines from the CentOS rpm.spec are: 

rm -f $RPM_BUILD_ROOT/%{rpmhome}/{perldeps.pl,perl.*,pythond*}
rm -f $RPM_BUILD_ROOT/%{_fileattrsdir}/{perl*,python*}

Please make sure your not removing additional files that should not be removed. Please notice it's removing "pythond*" not "python*"
